A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 2025 as Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, autoimmune diseases occur when the immune system mistakenly attacks
3 healthy cells and tissues, affecting more than 50 million Americans and millions more
4 individuals worldwide; and
5 WHEREAS, there are over 100 identified autoimmune diseases, many of which
6 disproportionately impact women, who make up approximately 80 percent of individuals
7 affected; and
8 WHEREAS, systemic lupus erythematosus (lupus) disproportionately affects Black women,
9 who are at greater risk of experiencing more severe symptoms and are three times more
10 likely to develop the disease compared to women of other groups; and
11 WHEREAS, Black women are also at an increased risk for other autoimmune diseases,
12 including sarcoidosis and polymyositis, which can lead to severe health complications; and
