13 WHEREAS, autoimmune diseases contribute to significant health disparities for Black
14 women, resulting in a critical need for increased awareness, research, and access to equitable
15 healthcare; and
16 WHEREAS, Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month provides an opportunity to educate the
17 public and healthcare professionals about autoimmune diseases, their impact on Black
18 women, and the importance of early detection and intervention; and
19 WHEREAS, supporting organizations dedicated to autoimmune disease advocacy, education,
20 and research is essential to improving outcomes for those affected.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
22 recognize March 2025 as Autoimmune Disease Awareness Month and acknowledge the
23 disproportionate impact of autoimmune diseases on Black women.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
25 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
26 press.
